description: Screenshots: http://imgcouch.com/image/VyA3 http://imgcouch.com/image/VfEZ http://imgcouch.com/image/Vuk1 IMDB: http://www.imdb.com/title/tt3530232/ Info: John Oliver won an Emmy for his work as a writer on "The Daily Show With Jon Stewart," but it wasn't until he guest-hosted that show in the summer of 2013 that HBO took notice of his "singular perspective and distinct voice." Thanks to that memorable gig, Oliver gets to show off his talent in front of HBO's camera on "Last Week Tonight." The late-night series sees the British comic review what happened the past seven days in news, politics and current events, all with a heavy dose of satire, of course. Oliver hosted a stand-up show for four seasons on Comedy Central, and he was also responsible for co-writing and co-presenting the popular weekly satirical podcast "The Bugle." First episode date: April 27, 2014 Narrated by: David Kaye Writers: John Oliver, Josh Gondelman, Tim Carvell, Kevin Avery, MORE Awards: Peabody Award, MORE Executive producers: John Oliver, Tim Carvell, Liz Stanton, Jon Thoday, James Taylor
